5:
Come, Lilith. Join me for an
excursion!
14:
You do remember what I said
before, do you not? No amount of
work will change the inevitable.
16:
Your time would be better spent
elsewhere. The Silver Woods will
soon reach its end, and
Pandemonium and the abyss are
not far behind.
19:
You bring up a good point, but I'm
not sure where we'll find new places
to relocate to...
23:
Why, "elsewhere," of course. Even if
we must defy the heavens above,
this is a duty we vowed to see
through.
27:
*sigh* So your excuse this time is
that we'll be out "surveying." You
truly have an excuse for everything,
don't you?
30:
Well, what exactly is it that you need
me to do?
35:
Aid me in selecting a
summer-appropriate outfit.
39:
How does that relate to surveying in
any way?! Besides, aren't there
others more suited to such a task?
42:
I'm afraid not. You see, I seek an
outfit befitting of a naive girl who
knows little of the world.
45: I shall be counting on you, Lilith.
49:
Excuse me? What did you mean by
what you just said?!
65:
The other day, I helped Estel select a
new outfit, which ended up being a
much-needed bit of stress relief...
67:
But ever since, she's been
disappearing off to
who-knows-where.
72:
Hmm... Well, despite how she acts,
she's still just a thirteen-year-old,
right? Maybe she's out exploring the
town.
75:
While it's true that she is curious
about the world...
78:
Given that she is still searching for a
way to efficiently increase the
population of her people...
87:
Ah, don't misunderstand! Her intent
is to solve various societal and
government issues...
90:
But she can be rather reckless in her
pursuit of satisfying her curiosity.
96:
Someone should check up on her
before we have a diplomatic issue
on our hands!
114:
He seems like an interesting guy...
Wonder how they know each other.
123: I'll hold him still while you swing.
128:
I really think you guys are jumping
the gun here!
132:
What manner of tomfoolery are you
lot up to?
135:
If you wish to join us, then come. I'm
certain you won't be disappointed
by what you find.
143:
Oh, I wouldn't go so far as calling
myself that. I'm just a person who
enjoys painting.
145:
Every summer, I hole up in this cabin
trying to portray the theme of an
endless summerin the form of a
young girl surrounded by sunflowers.
147:
Imagine my surprise when this year
an actual girl came tumbling out of
the sky and into the field of
sunflowers I was painting.
149:
My curiosity was piqued by these
unique-looking flowers. They do not
exist in our world.
152:
Haha, she says things like that with
such conviction that I could almost
believe another world actually exists.
154:
I must admit, I was captivated by
Ariel the second I gazed upon her.
156:
Something in her eyes spoke to me...
Something that conveyed the
"endless" part I've been searching
for...
161:
But over the course of hundreds of
years, like a drop of water slowly
molding the form of a boulder.
164:
I wish to see how mortals differ from
us when they create art, which is
how I found myself agreeing to this
distraction.
167:
A distraction, huh? Haha, I suppose
it's no surprise that's how you see
this.
170:
So you've become a model. I am
reminded of how I, too, once posed
for court painters
173:
Wait, the girl in this painting doesn't
appear to be an elf.
177:
That is the original model. At least,
that is what I presume. Am I correct,
Gwynn?
180:
Yeah... It's a little embarrassing to
admit, but this girl was my first love.
182:
She's no longer with us. This is the
only way I can still see heran
image painted from what remains
in my memories.
194:
That did not sound pleasant. Is there
something wrong with your lungs?
197:
Haha, are you worried about me?
There's no need. More importantly,
I've finished!
199: My last work... It's yours, Ariel!
202: I see. So it is finally finished.
214:
Are you sure you wish to hear my
opinion?
220:
You should not push yourself any
further. This was a unique
experience, and I thank you for it.
228:
T-tell me... What do you think... of my
art?
231:
Do you speak of these countless
paintings of a girl surrounded by
sunflowers?
234:
Or of the one you just painted?
Though I must admit, I cannot tell
the difference between them all.
241:
I never expected this to be more dull
than even the paintings of elves. My
apologies for expecting more than
you were capable of giving.
244:
No, hold on! Give me one more
chance! Please, just one more!
246:
My next painting will more than
meet your expectations! I swear it!
249: Is that so? Now this is interesting.
253:
Struggle with all you have, and show
me the eternity you seek. I shall
witness it all!
